The paper deals with properties of Boolean and pseudo-Boolean functions, which are fundamental concepts in computer science. The use of partial derivatives and lattice derivatives suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses classification and forbidden sections, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study of monotonicity in functions is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
